### Description

After upgrading from Angular 15 to Angular 17, custom class decorators are not working in the library.

For example, this is the class decorator:
```typescript
export function MyDecorator<T extends { new(...args: any[]): {} }>(originalConstructor: T) {
  // Return a new constructor function
  const newConstructor = class extends originalConstructor {
    // You can modify or extend the constructor here
    constructor(...args: any[]) {
      console.log("new constructor");
      super(...args);
    }
  };

  // copying static methods
  Object.entries(Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptors(originalConstructor))
    .filter(([, descriptor]) => descriptor.writable !== false)
    .forEach(([propName]) => {
      const propertyD = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(originalConstructor, propName);
      if (propertyD) {
        Object.defineProperty(
          newConstructor,
          propName,
          propertyD
        );
      }
    });

  return newConstructor;
}
``` 


This is my-lib.service.ts which used @MyDecorator
```typescript
import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';
import { MyDecorator } from './my-decorator';

@MyDecorator
@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class MyLibService {

  constructor() {
    console.log("old Constructor")
  }

  getHeros() {
    console.log("my lib service get heros");
  }
}

``` 

The result of angular 15
![image](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/6194868/716f7ec0-4dd6-4f5e-b210-017773f45cf4)

The result of angular 17
![image](https://github.com/angular/angular/assets/6194868/55e507ba-2e1b-4e31-895f-e3e388c45b4f)

This issue only occurs in libraries of Angular 17, custom class decorator works fine in main application.

The source code:
